<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aerie on 05-03-2001 02:30 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">While I don't agree with how Trawma said her points, she nailed the problem on the head.

 [QUOTE]Trawma said:
There are a lot of things in EQ that I will never get the chance to do, as in life. Who cares? No one.[/QUOTE]

How important is the sprinkler to you?

How far will you go to get your sprinkler?

 [QUOTE]Georgia said:
Uber guilds will crush people who are in smaller guilds and haven't cleared Veeshan's Peak.[/QUOTE]

Let me tell you a story. I was doing steps for druid/ranger epic in Greater Faydark. I needed to spawn a mob and give her an item. She (Faelin Bloodbriar) is a rare spawn, and would require anywhere from 0 min to 6 hours of camping.

I finally managed to spawn her. (requires clearing an orc pawn every 6 minutes like a clockwork.) Someone from not an uber guild came right up to her, gave her the item and despawned her. He knew I was there, and he very well could have guess why I was there. What did he do? Despawn Faelin and made me wait longer. Steal my spawn and crush me, to borrow your words.

How much are you willing to go for [b]YOUR[/b] sprinkler?

 [QUOTE]Georgia further says: 
Everyone deserves the epic if he/she is willing enough to put in the time, effort, and devotion worthy of holding such a weapon.[/QUOTE]

Fact is that there are several dozens of clerics on each server, all waiting for Mr. Ragerfire to rear his ugly face now. Only one of them can have it. All of them have put in roughly equal amount of timee and effort up to that point. Bickering ensures when he does spawn, and the people who are willing to sacrifice the most come up with the heart. (be it time, effort, or integrity)

I will be fairly blunt. If you want the sprinkler that bad, and your server atmosphere is "might makes it right," then why not get "might"? If you want the sprinkler that bad, why don't you go join that guild? 

You didn't, because the sprinkler is not worth compromising your personal ties to the people you know. Take a step back and look at it again. No item in the game is worth that much.

Go ahead and speak to Verant about this very real and valid problem. But don't say you have no way of obtaining the sprinkler, because you do have a way. It's just that it's the path you detest taking.

(edited to make reading easier)

[This message has been edited by Aerie (edited 05-03-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
